<COREF ID="7" TYPE="IDENT">The United Nations Security Council</COREF> decided on <COREF ID="5" TYPE="IDENT">the 13th</COREF> to hold a secret meeting on the 14th , discussing the Gulf conflict .
For several weeks , <COREF ID="6" TYPE="IDENT">countries such as Cuba , Yemen , etc.</COREF> have been asking the to hold a formal meeting .
<COREF ID="6" TYPE="IDENT">They</COREF> believe that air attacks made on Iraq by multinational forces headed by American forces exceeded the authorization limits of <COREF ID="7" TYPE="IDENT">the Security Council</COREF> .
However , countries such as <COREF ID="4" TYPE="IDENT">the US</COREF> , <COREF ID="1" TYPE="IDENT">the UK</COREF> , etc. are against holding a formal meeting .
